President Muhammadu Buhari, on Friday, lamented over the state of Nigeria’s economy. Buhari lamented that he is not comfortable with the country’s current economy. The president spoke during an interview on Nigerian Television Authority, NTA. Southeast Economy: Ohanaeze takes Buhari government to task, hails Ikpeazu, Ugwuanyi He also urged Nigerians to take up Agriculture in a bid to boost the economy. According to Buhari: “I’m not comfortable with Nigeria’s economy and that is why I’m working hard to get foreign nations to invest in our country. “We need people to go back to the farm, there are people leaving their air conditioned office and going back to the farm and this has helped us as a country.” Nigeria’s economy will shut down in 32 weeks – Primate Ayodele warns Buhari